handlung von Lizenzen kleiner Formen in sowie jenseits kodifizierter Poetiken des Barock. Vor dem Hintergrund historischer Umbrüche werden die Potenziale u. die Attraktivität barocker Kleinformen für die literarische Moderne herausgestellt, in der das Barock zur maßgeblichen Reflexionsepoche wird.  aThis volume examines the history of short literary forms between Baroque and modernist literature. The essays look at how the license of short literary forms was negotiated within and beyond the codified poetics of the Baroque period. Against the backdrop of historical upheaval, they identify the potential and the attractiveness of these works for literary modernism, which takes the Baroque era as its defining object of reflection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aBarock. 4aBarockrezeption. 4aLiteratur/Kleinform. 4aWissensgeschichte. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aBaroque.  ahistory of knowledge.  aliterature/short literary forms.  areception of the Baroque period.1 aBrasch, Anna S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrey, Christiane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHock, Jonas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHohlweck, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Matthias, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aResch, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRitter, Nils C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRitter, Nils C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchagerl, Jasper, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb